Police in Nyeri County arrested a student after suspecting he was carrying explosives. County Commissioner Fredrick Shisia said the Nyeri National Polytechnic student had strapped unidentified gadgets around his belly, waist and chest. "He was found near Dedan Kimathi University of Technology's entrance and he looked suspicious. He was arrested by police on patrol and taken to Kabiruini police post," Mr Shisia said on Friday. The items found in his possession included batteries and some electronic parts of a radio. Mr Shisia said the student told police he was carrying electric toning equipment used for physical fitness. The devices were destroyed by bomb experts as the student was handed over to the Directorate of Criminal Investigations and Anti-Terror Police Unit for further questioning.  